/17-Solo-Leveling-ReAwakening-credit-Solo-Leveling-Animation-Partners@1200x900.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="Solo Leveling ReAwakening photo by Solo Leveling Animation Partners" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/17-Solo-Leveling-ReAwakening-credit-Solo-Leveling-Animation-Partners@1200x900.jpg 1200w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/17-Solo-Leveling-ReAwakening-credit-Solo-Leveling-Animation-Partners@1200x900-400x300.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/17-Solo-Leveling-ReAwakening-credit-Solo-Leveling-Animation-Partners@1200x900-800x600.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/17-Solo-Leveling-ReAwakening-credit-Solo-Leveling-Animation-Partners@1200x900-696x522.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/17-Solo-Leveling-ReAwakening-credit-Solo-Leveling-Animation-Partners@1200x900-1068x801.jpg 1068w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></p><p> Hit anime <a href="https://www.nme.com/series/solo-leveling"><em>Solo Leveling</em></a> has surpassed a genre classic in terms of reviews on platform <a href="https://www.nme.com/brands/crunchyroll">Crunchyroll</a> , despite only having 23 episodes aired so far.</p><ul><li> <strong>READ MORE:</strong> <a href="https://www.nme.com/reviews/tv-reviews/solo-leveling-season-1-review-3611630"><em>Solo Leveling</em> review – believe the hype</a></li></ul><p> <a href="https://www.nme.com/series/one-piece"><em>One Piece</em></a> , the wildly popular series with over 1,100 episodes, previously held the record for most reviews on the platform with 596,000. Despite having a fraction of that runtime, Solo Leveling has overtaken it with<a href="https://www.crunchyroll.com/series/GDKHZEJ0K/solo-leveling" target="_blank" rel="noopener">603,000</a> .</p><p> For comparison, long-running favourite <a href="https://www.nme.com/series/demon-slayer"><em>Demon Slayer</em></a> has 587,000 reviews, while the epic <a href="https://www.nme.com/series/attack-on-titan"><em>Attack On Titan</em></a> ended with 354,000 reviews. This metric is not a precise indicator of audience size, or hours watched, but it goes some way to illustrating the immense popularity of <em>Solo Leveling</em> early into its history.</p><p> Based on the Korean web novel by Chugong, the hit anime series takes place in a realm of gifted hunters and monsters. In this world, weak hunter Sung Jinwoo is given extraordinary strength through a mysterious programme, which kickstarts a journey across the various dungeons to discover the true source of his power. </p><p><iframe loading="lazy" title="Solo Leveling Season 2 -Arise from the Shadow- |官方拖车" width="696" height="392" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/byJ7pxxhaDY?feature=oembed&enablejsapi=1" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen></iframe></p><p></p><p> The show is produced by A-1 Pictures and directed by Shunsuke Nakashige, with Noboru Kimura writing the scripts, Tomoko Sudo designing the characters and Hiroyuji Sawano composing the music.</p><p> The first season aired from January to March 2024 to critical and fan acclaim. A second season, entitled <em>Arise From The Shadow</em> , premiered in January 2025. There is also a Korean drama adaptation in development.</p><p> Recently, the show&#39;s voice actor Taito Ban (Sung Jin-woo) has built excitement for season two of the anime show, by <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/tv/solo-leveling-star-teases-dark-direction-for-remaining-season-two-episodes-3827583">promising a “darker direction” than fans will have seen before</a> .</p><p> “(Jin-woo) has undergone a huge change, both mentally and physically” he said, adding that the character may be heading in an unexpected direction. “All of these levelling ups have meaning. Story-wise, Jin-woo&#39;s path is not bright, and he is heading in a dark direction”.</p><p> The post <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/tv/solo-leveling-beats-one-piece-streaming-record-despite-only-releasing-23-episodes-so-far-3846811">&#39;Solo Leveling&#39; beats &#39;One Piece&#39; streaming record despite only releasing 23 episodes so far</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ;
